281
00:11:37.800 --> 00:11:39.220
to engage in a duel.

282
00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:40.020
What?

283
00:11:40.420 --> 00:11:42.340
Death for the thrust of a sword?

284
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:46.080
How human nature has degenerated!

285
00:11:46.540 --> 00:11:49.680
Nay, the restriction is but for one week,

286
00:11:50.100 --> 00:11:51.200
the carnival week.

287
00:11:51.600 --> 00:11:53.400
You will have the rest of the year

288
00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:54.940
to enjoy yourself.

289
00:11:54.940 --> 00:11:55.920
A whole week?

290
00:11:56.380 --> 00:11:58.160
It is hard for one who has nothing

291
00:11:58.160 --> 00:12:00.200
but a hot temper to warm his thin

292
00:12:00.200 --> 00:12:00.620
blood.

293
00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:05.520
But you, who are, by the by, Don

294
00:12:05.520 --> 00:12:06.980
José, what are you?

295
00:12:07.400 --> 00:12:07.880
I?

296
00:12:08.460 --> 00:12:10.040
I am nothing.

297
00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:11.000
Nothing?

298
00:12:11.640 --> 00:12:14.580
Then we are still on an equality.

299
00:12:14.940 --> 00:12:18.180
Enter Lazario and Parcolo, a water-carrier.

300
00:12:18.840 --> 00:12:20.300
Left second entrance.

301
00:12:20.860 --> 00:12:21.580
They get centre.

302
00:12:21.580 --> 00:12:24.980
Nay, Signior Lazario, do not spurn my good

303
00:12:24.980 --> 00:12:25.440
offices.

304
00:12:25.720 --> 00:12:27.300
You have been cruelly used.

305
00:12:27.440 --> 00:12:28.580
That's the truth, aunt.

306
00:12:28.800 --> 00:12:30.720
Thank you, comrade, thank you.

307
00:12:31.640 --> 00:12:33.340
Think me not proud or ungrateful.

308
00:12:34.040 --> 00:12:37.120
I have but one desire, and that is

309
00:12:37.120 --> 00:12:38.380
to die.

310
00:12:38.760 --> 00:12:39.620
Crosses left.

311
00:12:39.900 --> 00:12:41.580
Don José muses aside.

312
00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:43.980
To die before your beard grows?

313
00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:46.560
Ay, sir, he would drown himself.

314
00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:47.400
How?

315
00:12:48.440 --> 00:12:48.940
Drown?

316
00:12:49.440 --> 00:12:50.080
In water?

317
00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:53.100
Exchange this bright and lovely earth for

318
00:12:53.100 --> 00:12:54.160
muddy water?

319
00:12:54.340 --> 00:12:56.420
The thought, aunt, gives one the ague.

320
00:12:57.160 --> 00:12:59.440
At your age to wish for death, you,

321
00:12:59.620 --> 00:13:02.520
you can't be plagued by creditors.

322
00:13:03.240 --> 00:13:05.680
No, Signior, I am an apprentice to the

323
00:13:05.680 --> 00:13:08.320
armourer, who has in charge of the aqua

324
00:13:08.320 --> 00:13:09.780
-buses or the royal guards.

325
00:13:09.940 --> 00:13:11.860
Well, there's no reason that you should

326
00:13:11.860 --> 00:13:12.900
drown yourself.

327
00:13:13.160 --> 00:13:16.260
No, Signior, but this morning, under the

328
00:13:16.260 --> 00:13:18.680
pretext that the arms were neglected, the

329
00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:21.160
captain ordered me to receive fifty lashes.

330
00:13:21.880 --> 00:13:22.840
Don Cesar indignantly.

331
00:13:23.460 --> 00:13:24.000
Fifty?

332
00:13:24.520 --> 00:13:26.160
It was not the number, Signior.

333
00:13:26.660 --> 00:13:30.060
I do not mind suffering, but one blow

334
00:13:30.060 --> 00:13:31.220
is too much to bear.

335
00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:34.560
Don Cesar crosses to Don José right.

336
00:13:34.840 --> 00:13:38.200
The boy is a true Spaniard, familiarly.

337
00:13:38.420 --> 00:13:40.960
We, we must speak in his favour, Don

338
00:13:40.960 --> 00:13:41.260
José.

339
00:13:41.880 --> 00:13:44.560
My lieutenant interceded for me, but in

340
00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:45.340
vain, Signior.

341
00:13:45.340 --> 00:13:48.400
Possibly, but he will not refuse the request

342
00:13:48.400 --> 00:13:50.960
of such noble advocates as ourselves.

343
00:13:51.620 --> 00:13:52.980
Takes Don José's arm.

344
00:13:53.160 --> 00:13:53.920
Don José.

345
00:13:54.420 --> 00:13:55.500
Pardon me.

346
00:13:56.120 --> 00:13:57.520
Releasing his arm gently.

347
00:13:57.640 --> 00:14:00.140
But at present there are reasons for my

348
00:14:00.140 --> 00:14:01.740
non-interference.

349
00:14:02.320 --> 00:14:03.240
Oh, very well.

350
00:14:03.480 --> 00:14:06.420
Then the boy must be dependent upon my

351
00:14:06.420 --> 00:14:07.520
influence alone.

352
00:14:08.020 --> 00:14:08.960
Footsteps heard.

353
00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:12.100
Lazzarillo looks off left upper entrance.

354
00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:15.000
Ah, I am pursued.

355
00:14:15.580 --> 00:14:18.060
I shall be again degraded.

356
00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:18.500
Going.

357
00:14:18.780 --> 00:14:19.060
Stay.

358
00:14:19.680 --> 00:14:21.220
Place yourself behind me.

359
00:14:21.500 --> 00:14:22.980
We will defend you.

360
00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:23.520
We?

361
00:14:24.180 --> 00:14:25.540
Don Cesar bows.

362
00:14:25.800 --> 00:14:28.940
Yes, Don Cesar and his sword.

363
00:14:29.340 --> 00:14:30.600
About to draw.

364
00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:33.280
You forget the royal edict.

365
00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:37.300
The about to utter an imprecation removes

366
00:14:37.300 --> 00:14:37.880
his hat.

367
00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:39.900
But it is the carnival week.

368
00:14:39.900 --> 00:14:40.940
Trumpet.

369
00:14:41.800 --> 00:14:44.420
Enter captain and soldiers, left second

370
00:14:44.420 --> 00:14:44.980
entrance.

371
00:14:45.500 --> 00:14:46.960
They cross it back to right.

372
00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:48.100
There is your prisoner.

373
00:14:48.540 --> 00:14:49.100
Secure him.

374
00:14:49.280 --> 00:14:50.060
Points to Lazzarillo.

375
00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:52.700
Don Cesar interfering humbly.

376
00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:54.100
One moment, captain.

377
00:14:54.580 --> 00:14:58.080
Allow me, suffer me to humbly intercede for

378
00:14:58.080 --> 00:14:59.300
this young delinquent.

379
00:14:59.740 --> 00:15:01.940
Captain to soldiers, who pause, and not

380
00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:03.100
regarding Don Cesar.

381
00:15:03.520 --> 00:15:05.480
Soldiers, why do you pause?

382
00:15:05.600 --> 00:15:06.840
The soldiers advance.

383
00:15:06.840 --> 00:15:09.820
Oh, mercy, captain, mercy.

384
00:15:10.120 --> 00:15:11.940
You do not hear him, captain.

385
00:15:12.140 --> 00:15:14.240
The poor lad soothes for mercy.

386
00:15:15.060 --> 00:15:15.960
Let me.

387
00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:17.240
Uncovering.

388
00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:21.300
Join with him in supplicating pardon.

389
00:15:21.840 --> 00:15:23.340
Captain to Lazzarillo.

390
00:15:23.520 --> 00:15:25.060
Back to your duty, sirrah.

391
00:15:25.480 --> 00:15:28.480
I heed neither your tears nor the mouthings

392
00:15:28.480 --> 00:15:29.740
of this saddish mummer.

393
00:15:29.940 --> 00:15:30.840
Don Cesar indignantly.

394
00:15:31.840 --> 00:15:32.360
What?

395
00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:34.000
Recollecting himself.

396
00:15:34.280 --> 00:15:35.800
That cursed edict.

397
00:15:35.800 --> 00:15:38.760
Oh, if it were not the hanging week.

398
00:15:39.060 --> 00:15:39.700
Calmly.

399
00:15:39.800 --> 00:15:42.880
But, captain, if he returns no blows.

400
00:15:43.680 --> 00:15:47.020
See, tears, they are not easily wrung from

401
00:15:47.020 --> 00:15:48.340
so brave a heart.

402
00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:50.040
Captain crosses right.

403
00:15:50.480 --> 00:15:51.480
Pardon, captain.

404
00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:53.280
Detains him by the cloak.

405
00:15:53.980 --> 00:15:55.380
Captain snatching it away.

406
00:15:55.560 --> 00:15:56.380
Unhand me.

407
00:15:56.560 --> 00:15:57.660
Take stage right.

408
00:15:58.420 --> 00:15:59.800
Don Cesar indignantly.

409
00:16:00.540 --> 00:16:00.980
Dare.

410
00:16:01.600 --> 00:16:02.240
Recollecting.

411
00:16:02.380 --> 00:16:05.260
Oh, that edict, that cursed edict.

412
00:16:05.260 --> 00:16:07.460
Don Jose aside to Don Cesar.

413
00:16:07.900 --> 00:16:09.360
Centre and going up.

414
00:16:09.660 --> 00:16:11.620
Hard words, Don Cesar.

415
00:16:11.960 --> 00:16:13.280
Don Cesar to captain.

416
00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:14.360
One word more.

417
00:16:15.340 --> 00:16:17.480
You are a gentleman and a soldier.

418
00:16:18.240 --> 00:16:18.800
So am I.

419
00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:22.120
I have pledged my honour to protect this

420
00:16:22.120 --> 00:16:23.320
boy, you understand.

421
00:16:23.960 --> 00:16:26.880
I have soothed, implored you to forgive.

422
00:16:27.220 --> 00:16:29.240
Crosses round to right with Lazzarillo.

423
00:16:29.460 --> 00:16:30.820
You have my answer.

424
00:16:31.280 --> 00:16:31.960
Crosses left.

425
00:16:32.080 --> 00:16:32.280
No.

426
00:16:32.280 --> 00:16:36.880
What I solicited in vain, I must now

427
00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:37.700
compel.

428
00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:38.760
Insolent.

429
00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:39.540
Enough.

430
00:16:39.780 --> 00:16:42.280
In spite of the royal edict, I must

431
00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:45.220
have the amende, my noble captain.

432
00:16:45.580 --> 00:16:45.860
How?

433
00:16:46.160 --> 00:16:46.580
How?

434
00:16:46.960 --> 00:16:50.100
With my sword, which will ennoble yours by

435
00:16:50.100 --> 00:16:50.800
the contact.

436
00:16:51.280 --> 00:16:53.480
I am Don Cesar de Bazan.

437
00:16:53.840 --> 00:16:54.960
Replacing his hat.

438
00:16:55.100 --> 00:16:58.160
Count de Garofa, possessing the right to

439
00:16:58.160 --> 00:17:00.920
remain covered in the presence of the king.

440
00:17:00.920 --> 00:17:05.579
I have soothed you, humbly soothed you, and

441
00:17:05.579 --> 00:17:08.920
you have insulted me and the royal edict.

442
00:17:09.599 --> 00:17:10.119
Draws.

443
00:17:10.280 --> 00:17:10.940
A challenge.

444
00:17:11.440 --> 00:17:14.599
Yes, which you will accept if you have

445
00:17:14.599 --> 00:17:16.460
either shame or courage.

446
00:17:16.780 --> 00:17:18.180
You shall not doubt the latter.

447
00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:20.900
Follow me and receive the proof.

448
00:17:21.160 --> 00:17:22.660
Exit left upper entrance.

449
00:17:23.540 --> 00:17:24.480
Lazzarillo right.

450
00:17:24.839 --> 00:17:26.099
You fight for me.

451
00:17:26.500 --> 00:17:27.079
Oh no.

452
00:17:27.820 --> 00:17:29.320
I will return, Don Cesar.

453
00:17:29.320 --> 00:17:31.480
Don Cesar right of centre.

454
00:17:31.640 --> 00:17:33.740
You shall, my gallant lad, to your

455
00:17:33.740 --> 00:17:36.200
lieutenant, who would have spared you the

456
00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:37.400
ignominy of a blow.

457
00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:41.120
Be patient, and in ten minutes I will

458
00:17:41.120 --> 00:17:42.760
make him a captain.

459
00:17:43.300 --> 00:17:45.720
Excellent Albert Don José left upper

460
00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:46.220
entrance.

461
00:17:46.700 --> 00:17:50.260
Don Cesar was the best swordsman in Madrid.

462
00:17:50.960 --> 00:17:53.720
Should he retain his cunning, my plans will

463
00:17:53.720 --> 00:17:55.860
soon have a happy consummation.

464
00:17:55.860 --> 00:17:57.900
The edict enforced.

465
00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:00.920
Don Cesar's reckless nature will make him

466
00:18:00.920 --> 00:18:03.380
the easy means of Maritana's advancement.

467
00:18:04.060 --> 00:18:08.200
Ah, here comes the fair enslaver of the

468
00:18:08.200 --> 00:18:08.640
king.

469
00:18:09.160 --> 00:18:10.440
Enter Maritana left.

470
00:18:10.980 --> 00:18:13.000
She wears a scarf of gaudy colours.

471
00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:16.640
Again the queen has smiled upon me.

472
00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:19.720
It is no idle fantasy that fills my

473
00:18:19.720 --> 00:18:20.240
brain.

474
00:18:20.660 --> 00:18:23.260
Some lucky accident may place me at the

475
00:18:23.260 --> 00:18:24.520
height of my ambition.

476
00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:26.380
Si, Don José.

477
00:18:26.860 --> 00:18:28.160
Ah, señor.

478
00:18:29.100 --> 00:18:31.700
I would fain know what pleasant thoughts

479
00:18:31.700 --> 00:18:35.860
give birth to such bright smiles, Maritana.

480
00:18:36.220 --> 00:18:38.660
The queen, señor, the queen.

481
00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:42.060
You see, I have not been a niggard

482
00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:42.840
of your gift.

483
00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:44.340
She holds a scarf.

484
00:18:44.640 --> 00:18:46.860
And you think yourself rich in the

485
00:18:46.860 --> 00:18:48.660
possession of such a trifle?

486
00:18:49.440 --> 00:18:52.780
Confide in me and ere long the gayest

487
00:18:52.780 --> 00:18:55.820
lady of the court shall yield to you

488
00:18:55.820 --> 00:18:57.580
in splendour.

489
00:18:57.900 --> 00:18:59.400
Dare not listen to you.

490
00:18:59.760 --> 00:19:01.940
I dare not trust the longing of my

491
00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:02.620
heart.

492
00:19:03.060 --> 00:19:03.740
Wherefore?

493
00:19:04.320 --> 00:19:07.040
My roving life has taught me truth beyond

494
00:19:07.040 --> 00:19:09.460
the common experience of my years.

495
00:19:09.880 --> 00:19:12.240
I have seen the rich man's idol of

496
00:19:12.240 --> 00:19:15.120
today the outcast of tomorrow.

497
00:19:15.740 --> 00:19:16.420
No, no.

498
00:19:16.880 --> 00:19:17.560
Mournfully.

499
00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:20.680
My destiny is known to me.

500
00:19:21.200 --> 00:19:23.420
You do not believe your own prophecies.

501
00:19:24.060 --> 00:19:26.600
You may gull the dullards who bribe you

502
00:19:26.600 --> 00:19:30.140
to promise fortune, but you know yourself a

503
00:19:30.140 --> 00:19:30.520
cheat.

504
00:19:31.160 --> 00:19:33.840
I will show you my skill in palmistry.

505
00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:35.320
Takes her hand.

506
00:19:35.540 --> 00:19:37.950
Tomorrow you shall be a countess.

507
00:19:38.440 --> 00:19:39.620
Maritana delighted.

508
00:19:40.060 --> 00:19:41.380
A countess.

509
00:19:41.800 --> 00:19:42.620
Pauses.

510
00:19:43.180 --> 00:19:45.280
A countess but in name.

511
00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:47.960
By right of honourable alliance.

512
00:19:48.660 --> 00:19:50.720
You know me not, or you would not

513
00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:53.500
doubt my power to realise the hopes I

514
00:19:53.500 --> 00:19:54.160
have awakened.

515
00:19:55.100 --> 00:19:58.240
You rescued but now a stranger from the

516
00:19:58.240 --> 00:19:59.660
extortions of your band.

517
00:20:00.160 --> 00:20:00.940
Yes, yes.

518
00:20:01.300 --> 00:20:03.960
He saved me from insult, but I repaid

519
00:20:03.960 --> 00:20:05.320
the debt I owed him.

520
00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:09.100
Though now a ruined spendthrift, he is of

521
00:20:09.100 --> 00:20:10.520
noble lineage.

522
00:20:11.100 --> 00:20:13.340
He loves you, Maritana.

523
00:20:13.340 --> 00:20:15.620
Maritana appears affected.

524
00:20:16.240 --> 00:20:17.460
Indeed, señor.

525
00:20:18.320 --> 00:20:20.720
I have promised to be his advocate.

526
00:20:21.360 --> 00:20:23.640
Should you consent to share his name and

527
00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:27.320
fortunes, I will restore him to position.

528
00:20:27.840 --> 00:20:28.900
Have you the power?

529
00:20:29.360 --> 00:20:32.880
Don José, the favourite minister of Charles

530
00:20:32.880 --> 00:20:35.260
of Spain, could do much more.

531
00:20:35.520 --> 00:20:36.660
And you are?

532
00:20:36.660 --> 00:20:40.640
Don José, commissioned by the Queen to raise

533
00:20:40.640 --> 00:20:43.380
Maritana to the rank she covets.

534
00:20:43.800 --> 00:20:44.480
Indeed.

535
00:20:45.440 --> 00:20:47.380
Then I have not dreamed.

536
00:20:47.900 --> 00:20:50.320
I have not trusted to phantom hopes.

537
00:20:50.640 --> 00:20:54.520
Before tomorrow, I will prove their reality.

538
00:20:55.020 --> 00:20:55.880
Murmurs heard.

539
00:20:56.500 --> 00:20:58.280
Maritana appears overpowered.

540
00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:01.220
Don José looks off aside.

541
00:21:01.600 --> 00:21:04.040
Ah, fortune befriends me.

542
00:21:04.040 --> 00:21:08.060
Don César is the victor, and already in

543
00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:09.360
the hands of the Algazils.

544
00:21:10.040 --> 00:21:11.160
Music is heard.

545
00:21:11.940 --> 00:21:12.540
Aloud.

546
00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:14.500
Your hand, fair lady.

547
00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:17.260
Let me lead you to your honours.

548
00:21:18.020 --> 00:21:19.160
Excellent right.

549
00:21:22.200 --> 00:21:25.560
Four Algazils enter, conducting Don César.

550
00:21:26.080 --> 00:21:27.460
Lazarelle follows, weeping.

551
00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:31.040
The crowd of dancers, etc., appear by

552
00:21:31.040 --> 00:21:33.020
gesture to taunt Don César.

553
00:21:33.680 --> 00:21:34.860
He walks proudly.

554
00:21:35.660 --> 00:21:38.000
An officer and twelve soldiers enter from

555
00:21:38.000 --> 00:21:38.920
opposite side.

556
00:21:39.580 --> 00:21:41.880
Soldiers march round and clear crowd back

557
00:21:41.880 --> 00:21:44.240
right and left, and go off with Don

558
00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:46.260
César, upper entrance right.

559
00:21:46.880 --> 00:21:49.300
Crowd taunting him at end of course.

560
00:21:50.380 --> 00:21:52.780
Six soldiers cross from upper entrance left

561
00:21:52.780 --> 00:21:54.580
to right, down stage.

562
00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:57.760
Six ditto down left meet and charge crowd

563
00:21:57.760 --> 00:21:59.440
up and range right and left.

564
00:22:00.140 --> 00:22:02.980
All excellent upper entrance right at end of

565
00:22:02.980 --> 00:22:03.340
course.

566
00:22:03.340 --> 00:22:06.640
Clock chimes and strikes five at change of

567
00:22:06.640 --> 00:22:07.080
scene.

568
00:22:08.740 --> 00:22:09.880
Scene two.

569
00:22:10.620 --> 00:22:11.100
A prison.

570
00:22:11.780 --> 00:22:12.940
Doors right and left.

571
00:22:13.580 --> 00:22:14.420
Clock at work.

572
00:22:14.820 --> 00:22:15.920
A table and stools.

573
00:22:16.900 --> 00:22:19.040
Enter Pedro right and López left.

574
00:22:19.520 --> 00:22:20.120
Good news.

575
00:22:20.600 --> 00:22:21.500
Good news.

576
00:22:22.100 --> 00:22:24.700
The royal idiot has sent you a prisoner.

577
00:22:25.220 --> 00:22:26.660
Good news truly.

578
00:22:27.300 --> 00:22:29.200
It is now a week since I had

579
00:22:29.200 --> 00:22:32.300
the pleasure of turning a key upon anyone

580
00:22:32.300 --> 00:22:33.520
but my wife.

581
00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:36.260
But are you sure the news is true?

582
00:22:36.760 --> 00:22:37.080
True.

583
00:22:38.380 --> 00:22:39.700
I saw the jewel.

584
00:22:40.340 --> 00:22:42.460
I saw the hot-blooded raffler in the

585
00:22:42.460 --> 00:22:45.040
presence of the Alcad, who has been idle

586
00:22:45.040 --> 00:22:47.040
too long to let a chance escape him.

587
00:22:47.840 --> 00:22:48.080
Si.

588
00:22:48.900 --> 00:22:50.800
Here comes the prisoner.

589
00:22:51.560 --> 00:22:53.800
Enter Don César and Lázaro right.

590
00:22:54.520 --> 00:22:57.440
Two Alguazils and two soldiers appear at the

591
00:22:57.440 --> 00:22:57.780
door.

592
00:22:58.380 --> 00:23:01.200
And all excellent but Don César and Lázaro.

593
00:23:02.160 --> 00:23:02.680
Arrested.

594
00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:04.320
Tried and condemned.

595
00:23:05.020 --> 00:23:06.020
All within an hour.

596
00:23:07.180 --> 00:23:08.720
He has but two hours to live.

597
00:23:09.120 --> 00:23:10.680
Don César looking at clock.

598
00:23:10.880 --> 00:23:12.000
Two hours more.

599
00:23:12.560 --> 00:23:14.460
How the deuce am I to pass my

600
00:23:14.460 --> 00:23:14.960
time?

601
00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:17.320
I shall die of ennui.

602
00:23:17.760 --> 00:23:20.140
Takes a chair and sits left of centre.

603
00:23:20.880 --> 00:23:21.320
Pause.

604
00:23:21.460 --> 00:23:22.980
If you were in my place and had

605
00:23:22.980 --> 00:23:25.260
a couple of hours before you, how would

606
00:23:25.260 --> 00:23:26.320
you employ them?

607
00:23:26.560 --> 00:23:28.880
In recalling the hours of my past life.

608
00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:30.580
What, in two hours?

609
00:23:31.020 --> 00:23:33.700
You must be very ignorant of my biography.

610
00:23:34.540 --> 00:23:36.360
Recall my past errors?

611
00:23:36.600 --> 00:23:39.140
No, there is no time for that.

612
00:23:39.900 --> 00:23:40.980
I'll make my will.

613
00:23:41.780 --> 00:23:44.580
No, that would not consume two minutes.

614
00:23:45.160 --> 00:23:45.620
Oh, señor.

615
00:23:46.860 --> 00:23:49.000
Taking his hand and sobbing.

616
00:23:49.340 --> 00:23:50.920
I have been the cause of this.

617
00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:53.180
It is for me you are about to

618
00:23:53.180 --> 00:23:53.480
die.

619
00:23:54.520 --> 00:23:56.280
Is there no service by which I can

620
00:23:56.280 --> 00:23:57.220
show my regret?

621
00:23:57.220 --> 00:23:58.800
My gratitude?

622
00:23:59.640 --> 00:24:02.500
Yes, you can oblige me materially.

623
00:24:02.860 --> 00:24:05.600
Oh, how, say how?

624
00:24:05.960 --> 00:24:07.480
Clinging to his hand.

625
00:24:07.840 --> 00:24:10.160
By showing little more regard for my lace

626
00:24:10.160 --> 00:24:10.680
ruffle.

627
00:24:11.040 --> 00:24:12.880
See how you've torn it?

628
00:24:13.300 --> 00:24:16.280
Alas, is there no one to entreat your

629
00:24:16.280 --> 00:24:17.360
pardon from the king?

630
00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:20.260
No one has yet pleaded for you.

631
00:24:20.500 --> 00:24:23.400
Nay, boy, all are not so indifferent to

632
00:24:23.400 --> 00:24:24.040
my fate.

633
00:24:24.040 --> 00:24:27.360
There was one venerable old man who threw

634
00:24:27.360 --> 00:24:29.860
himself in the path of the king regardless

635
00:24:29.860 --> 00:24:32.360
of the wheels of the royal carriage or

636
00:24:32.360 --> 00:24:34.020
the hooves of the royal mules.

637
00:24:34.680 --> 00:24:37.960
He stretched forth his trembling hands while

638
00:24:37.960 --> 00:24:42.200
tears bedewed his aged cheeks and in accents

639
00:24:42.200 --> 00:24:45.980
broken by emotion he implored, Pardon,

640
00:24:46.420 --> 00:24:48.000
pardon for Don Caesar.

641
00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:51.880
Ah, it was the old count, your father.

642
00:24:51.880 --> 00:24:54.240
No, it was one of my creditors.

643
00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:56.140
See how wrong you were.

644
00:24:56.520 --> 00:24:57.980
What of all your noble friends and

645
00:24:57.980 --> 00:24:58.460
companions?

646
00:24:59.380 --> 00:25:01.120
Not one has come to visit you.

647
00:25:01.300 --> 00:25:03.500
A mark of their good feeling, Mauricio.

648
00:25:03.900 --> 00:25:05.240
Don José enters.

649
00:25:05.620 --> 00:25:07.940
To see me in my present position would

650
00:25:07.940 --> 00:25:09.740
be more than they could bear.

651
00:25:10.160 --> 00:25:12.800
So out of kindness they keep away.

652
00:25:13.320 --> 00:25:15.020
Don José coming down right.

653
00:25:15.700 --> 00:25:16.780
Accepting me.

654
00:25:17.060 --> 00:25:17.920
Don José.

655
00:25:18.780 --> 00:25:21.520
Lazarillo exit right door at a sign from

656
00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:22.120
Don José.

657
00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:23.940
You seem surprised.

658
00:25:24.400 --> 00:25:25.240
You wrong me.

659
00:25:25.800 --> 00:25:27.280
I was always your friend.

660
00:25:28.200 --> 00:25:31.060
And do I not prove my sincerity by

661
00:25:31.060 --> 00:25:33.120
coming to you when all is over?

662
00:25:33.440 --> 00:25:35.460
If your friendship was to be of any

663
00:25:35.460 --> 00:25:38.240
practical service you might have made your

664
00:25:38.240 --> 00:25:39.400
visit a little earlier.

665
00:25:40.140 --> 00:25:42.200
But I confess if I had looked for

666
00:25:42.200 --> 00:25:44.860
sympathy yours would have been the last I

667
00:25:44.860 --> 00:25:45.780
should have expected.

668
00:25:45.780 --> 00:25:48.240
I may yet be in time to serve

669
00:25:48.240 --> 00:25:48.480
you.

670
00:25:49.100 --> 00:25:51.440
You have but two hours to live.

671
00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:52.960
I beg your pardon.

672
00:25:53.480 --> 00:25:55.920
Looking at clock, which now is a quarter

673
00:25:55.920 --> 00:25:56.660
past five.

674
00:25:56.760 --> 00:25:58.460
It is an hour and three quarters.

675
00:25:59.220 --> 00:26:01.720
The error is of no consequence, but we

676
00:26:01.720 --> 00:26:03.860
may as well be right when we can,

677
00:26:04.040 --> 00:26:05.760
for life is very short.

678
00:26:06.160 --> 00:26:08.720
Yours may be long enough to enable us

679
00:26:08.720 --> 00:26:10.180
to understand each other.

680
00:26:10.580 --> 00:26:12.040
Come, let us sit.

681
00:26:12.400 --> 00:26:14.080
I wish to speak with you.

682
00:26:14.080 --> 00:26:15.280
With pleasure.

683
00:26:15.640 --> 00:26:16.100
They sit.

684
00:26:16.320 --> 00:26:18.580
For my time is all your own.

685
00:26:18.940 --> 00:26:20.480
Well then, Don Cesar.

686
00:26:20.820 --> 00:26:21.940
Well, Don José.

687
00:26:22.420 --> 00:26:24.240
If I had it in my power to

688
00:26:24.240 --> 00:26:27.580
grant any demand what would be your dying

689
00:26:27.580 --> 00:26:28.220
request?

690
00:26:28.500 --> 00:26:29.600
My dying request?

691
00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:31.700
To live, to be sure.

692
00:26:31.900 --> 00:26:34.980
As the king's favourite minister, and as

693
00:26:34.980 --> 00:26:37.400
your friend, if you will accept the

694
00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:40.540
conditions I am about to propose I swear

695
00:26:40.540 --> 00:26:44.020
to grant whatever you ask, always accepting

696
00:26:44.020 --> 00:26:44.660
life.

697
00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:46.900
That I cannot promise.

698
00:26:47.240 --> 00:26:49.780
It's awkward, as that happens to be almost

699
00:26:49.780 --> 00:26:53.080
the only thing I'm likely shortly to want.

700
00:26:53.360 --> 00:26:54.920
Is there nothing else?

701
00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:55.480
Nothing.

702
00:26:56.280 --> 00:26:57.600
Stay, you saw a boy.

703
00:26:57.960 --> 00:26:59.160
Did you not, as you entered?

704
00:26:59.460 --> 00:27:01.660
The one to whom you owe your present

705
00:27:01.660 --> 00:27:02.180
position?

706
00:27:02.640 --> 00:27:05.680
Yes, I believe I do owe him that,

707
00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:07.680
but I owe something to everybody.

708
00:27:08.360 --> 00:27:09.760
I should not like him to be at

709
00:27:09.760 --> 00:27:10.980
the mercy of the world when I am

710
00:27:10.980 --> 00:27:11.300
gone.

711
00:27:11.300 --> 00:27:12.780
Will you assist him?

712
00:27:13.400 --> 00:27:15.340
Yes, I will provide for him.

713
00:27:15.620 --> 00:27:16.260
That is kind.

714
00:27:16.880 --> 00:27:20.760
I will pay you beforehand with a thousand

715
00:27:20.760 --> 00:27:21.240
thanks.

716
00:27:21.660 --> 00:27:24.120
Have you nothing else to ask, consider?

717
00:27:24.560 --> 00:27:26.440
No, I think that's all.

718
00:27:26.560 --> 00:27:27.860
Don José aside.

719
00:27:28.140 --> 00:27:30.940
He will never exceed my plan for such

720
00:27:30.940 --> 00:27:32.480
a trifling recompense.

721
00:27:32.820 --> 00:27:33.380
Allowed.

722
00:27:33.760 --> 00:27:36.220
Don Cesar, have you thought of the manner

723
00:27:36.220 --> 00:27:37.180
of your death?

724
00:27:37.480 --> 00:27:39.740
Yes, I know all.

725
00:27:40.040 --> 00:27:40.520
Rises.

726
00:27:40.520 --> 00:27:41.320
A rope.

727
00:27:42.240 --> 00:27:44.840
Would that death come my sword or arquebus,

728
00:27:45.320 --> 00:27:46.240
but a rope.

729
00:27:47.340 --> 00:27:49.520
Yes, I think I have one request, Don

730
00:27:49.520 --> 00:27:49.900
José.

731
00:27:50.380 --> 00:27:51.040
Name it.

732
00:27:51.380 --> 00:27:53.520
I would bequeath the gallows to my

733
00:27:53.520 --> 00:27:56.780
creditors, but let me dispatched by the

734
00:27:56.780 --> 00:27:59.300
arquebuses of a dozen brave fellows.

735
00:28:00.420 --> 00:28:03.540
In short, let me die like a gentleman.

736
00:28:04.100 --> 00:28:06.120
You shall have your wish.

737
00:28:06.380 --> 00:28:07.380
You will not deceive?

738
00:28:07.380 --> 00:28:10.720
I swear it on the honour of a

739
00:28:10.720 --> 00:28:11.120
soldier.

740
00:28:11.480 --> 00:28:12.400
You give me new life.

741
00:28:13.080 --> 00:28:15.020
That is to say, you have taken away

742
00:28:15.020 --> 00:28:17.700
half the inconvenience of death, if I

743
00:28:17.700 --> 00:28:20.040
receive it at the hands of brave men.

744
00:28:20.660 --> 00:28:22.740
I should like to drink with the worthy

745
00:28:22.740 --> 00:28:23.300
fellows.

746
00:28:23.660 --> 00:28:24.560
Drink with them?

747
00:28:24.960 --> 00:28:27.220
You, the Count de Besan?

748
00:28:27.380 --> 00:28:29.360
I've drunk in worse company o' this.

749
00:28:29.980 --> 00:28:32.980
Besides, if I am their superior now, they

750
00:28:32.980 --> 00:28:34.820
will soon have the advantage of me.

751
00:28:34.820 --> 00:28:37.840
You promised to grant my wish.

752
00:28:38.440 --> 00:28:39.060
And I will.

753
00:28:39.460 --> 00:28:42.180
A banquet shall be prepared for you that

754
00:28:42.180 --> 00:28:44.900
shall recall the revels of past times.

755
00:28:45.260 --> 00:28:46.200
Is that all?

756
00:28:46.580 --> 00:28:47.320
Yes, that's all.

757
00:28:47.760 --> 00:28:48.960
And now for your conditions.

758
00:28:49.340 --> 00:28:51.380
What do you require of me?

759
00:28:51.840 --> 00:28:53.100
Both sit down.

760
00:28:53.540 --> 00:28:55.740
Not much for a man in your position.

761
00:28:56.180 --> 00:28:59.540
I simply require you to marry.

762
00:29:00.020 --> 00:29:01.900
Clock now at half-past five.

763
00:29:01.900 --> 00:29:02.360
Hmm.

764
00:29:03.220 --> 00:29:04.080
To marry?

765
00:29:05.020 --> 00:29:06.720
I don't see the use of that.

766
00:29:07.040 --> 00:29:08.320
What can be the good of it for

767
00:29:08.320 --> 00:29:09.660
an hour and a half?

768
00:29:09.920 --> 00:29:11.480
That is a mystery.

769
00:29:11.900 --> 00:29:12.920
A mystery indeed.

770
00:29:13.560 --> 00:29:15.700
It can't be for my fortune, because I

771
00:29:15.700 --> 00:29:18.500
have nothing to leave, except my debts and

772
00:29:18.500 --> 00:29:19.100
my name.

773
00:29:20.360 --> 00:29:20.700
Ah.

774
00:29:21.160 --> 00:29:23.060
My name has still some value.

775
00:29:23.840 --> 00:29:24.560
I see it all.

776
00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:28.200
Some woman wishes to be called a countess.

777
00:29:28.640 --> 00:29:29.740
Is it not so?

778
00:29:29.960 --> 00:29:30.900
It may be.

779
00:29:30.900 --> 00:29:32.420
Well, she shall have it.

780
00:29:32.920 --> 00:29:34.740
It is nothing to me.

781
00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:36.720
I want to fill up my time.

782
00:29:37.440 --> 00:29:40.480
Marriage is an occupation, and one may be

783
00:29:40.480 --> 00:29:41.540
as good as another.

784
00:29:42.140 --> 00:29:43.660
It's for so short a time.

785
00:29:44.200 --> 00:29:47.400
We can't have many matrimonial differences.

786
00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:50.780
You agree to confer the title of countess

787
00:29:50.780 --> 00:29:51.640
to Garofa?

788
00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:53.980
Together with my interest in the county of

789
00:29:53.980 --> 00:29:56.520
Garofa, if you can find I have any

790
00:29:56.520 --> 00:29:57.020
remaining.

791
00:29:57.460 --> 00:29:58.440
But by the by.
